      <h1 class="app-detail-title">Privacy Policy for Bulletin</h1>
      <p class="app-detail-tagline">Last updated: January 5, 2026</p>

      <div class="app-detail-content">
        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Overview</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">Bulletin is committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy policy explains our data practices for the Bulletin RSS feed reader application.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Data Collection</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description"><strong>We do not collect any data.</strong> Bulletin does not collect, store, transmit, or process any personal information or usage data from our users. We have no servers, no analytics, and no tracking.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Your Miniflux Server</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">Bulletin connects directly to your self-hosted Miniflux server using credentials you provide. All communication occurs directly between your device and your server. We do not have access to:</p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Your Miniflux server URL or credentials</li>
            <li>Your feed subscriptions or content</li>
            <li>Your reading history or preferences</li>
            <li>Any data stored on your Miniflux server</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Local Data Storage</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">All data in Bulletin is stored locally on your device, including:</p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>Your Miniflux server connection details</li>
            <li>Your reading preferences, themes, and settings</li>
            <li>Feed content cached for offline reading</li>
            <li>Your Read Later list and reading progress</li>
            <li>Feed filtering rules (blocklists and keeplists)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Third-Party Content</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">When you browse feeds, Bulletin may fetch images and content from third-party websites referenced in your feeds. These connections are made directly between your device and the content providers.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Analytics and Tracking</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">Bulletin does not use any analytics, tracking, or advertising services. We do not track your usage, behavior, or any other metrics. There are no third-party SDKs in the app.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Data Sharing</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">Since we do not collect any data, we do not share, sell, or transfer any data to third parties.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">Bulletin does not knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under the age of 13.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <h2 class="section-title">Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="app-detail-description">If you have any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at:</p>
          <p class="app-detail-description"><strong><a href="mailto:support@cosmique.io">support@cosmique.io</a></strong></p>
        </section>

        <section class="app-section">
          <p class="app-detail-description"><em>Bulletin is developed independently and is not affiliated with Miniflux or any RSS feed providers.</em></p>
        </section>
